The paper discusses the use of natural language processing and multimodal language in understanding humor, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the usage of visual and acoustic cues in producing humor, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) in the research. Additionally, the paper presents a framework for humor detection, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
